 Hungry Hippos]]\n*[[Jenga]]\n*[[KerPlunk (game)|Kerplunk]]\n*[[Krazy Maze]]\n*[[Operation (game)|Operation]]\n*[[Perfection (game)|Perfection]]\n*[[Polarity (game)|Polarity]]\n*[[Subbuteo]]\n*[[Twister (game)|Twister]]\n*[[Villa Paletti]]\n}}\n\n==Children's games==\nThe rules are easy to learn and the outcome is mostly or entirely due to chance.\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[Candy Land game|Candy Land]]\n*[[Catan| Catan Junior]]\n*[[Chicken Cha Cha Cha]]\n*[[Don't Break the Ice]]\n*[[Don't Wake Daddy]]\n*[[Forbidden Bridge]]\n*[[Hey Pa! There's a Goat on the Roof]]\n*[[Hi Ho! Cherry-O]]\n*[[Hungry Hungry Hippos]]\n*[[The Kids of Catan]]\n*[[Ludo (game)|Ludo]]\n*[[Mouse Trap (board game)|Mouse Trap]]\n*[[Snakes and ladders]] (aka Chutes and Ladders)\n*[[Sorry! (game)|Sorry!]]\n*[[Space Hop]]\n*[[Uncle Wiggily (board game)|Uncle Wiggily]]\n}}\n\n==Cooperative games==\n[[Cooperative game]]s in which all players need to work together to win.\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[Arkham Horror]]\n*[[Battlestar Galactica: The Board Game]]\n*[[Betrayal at House on the Hill]]\n*[[Castle Panic]]\n*[[Flash Point]]\n*[[Forbidden Island (game)|Forbidden Island]]\n*[[Freedom: The Underground Railroad]]\n*[[Gloomhaven]]\n*[[Hanabi (card game)|Hanabi]]\n*[[Just One (board game)|Just One]]\n*[[Lord of the Rings (board game)|Lord of the Rings]]\n*[[Pandemic (board game)|Pandemic]]\n*[[Sentinels of the Multiverse]]\n*[[Shadows Over Camelot|Shadows over Camelot]]\n*[[Space Alert]]\n*[[X-COM]]\n}}\n\n==Word games==\nThese games are based on construction of words to score points.\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[25 Words or Less]]\n*[[Acronymble]]\n*[[Aksharit]]\n*[[Alfapet]]\n*[[Bananagrams]]\n*[[Big Taboo]]\n*[[Kings Cribbage]]\n*[[Mad Gab]]\n*[[Pictionary]]\n*[[Probe (parlor game)|Probe]]\n*[[Scrabble]]\n*[[Thiruthamizh]]\n*[[Trickster (board game)|Trickster]]\n*[[UpWords]]\n*[[Words with Friends]]\n}}\n\n==Gaming systems==\nThese are sets that can be used to play multiple games.\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[Flibbix]]\n*[[Hanafuda]]\n*[[Icehouse pieces]]\n*[[Stonehenge (game)|Stonehenge]]\n}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Game of the Year]]\n*[[Games 100]]\n*[[List of board wargames]]\n*[[List of Japanese board games]]\n*[[List of mancala games]]\n*[[List of board game publishers]]\n*[[List of game manufacturers]]\n*[[List of cross and circle games]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.boardgamegeek.com Board Game Geek]\n*[http://www.boardgames.org Boardgames.org]\n*[http://zenseeker.net/BoardGames/ A Zen Guide to Board Games]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120729010243/http://gamerate.net/board-card/ Gamerate Game database]\n*[https://boardgamesland.com Board Games Land]\n\n[[Category:Lists of games|Board games]]\n[[Category:Board games|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\nThis is a list of [[board game]]s. This page classifies board games according to the concerns which might be uppermost for someone organizing a gaming event or party. See the article on [[game classification]] for other alternatives, or see [[:Category:Board games|Category:Board games]] for a list of board game articles.\n\n==Single-player board games==\nSome board games have solo variants, like [[Arkham Horror]] and [[Agricola (board game)|Agricola]]. Others are specifically designed for one player.\n\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n*[[Ambush!]]\n*[[B-17, Queen of the Skies]]\n*[[Fields of Fire (game)]]}}\n\n==Two-player abstract strategy games==\n{{main article|List of abstract strategy games}}\nIn [[abstract strategy game]]s, players know the entire game state at all times, and random generators such as dice are not used.\n\n==Two-player games==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n\n*[[Abalone (board game)|Abalone]]\n*[[Agon (game)|Agon]]\n*[[Android: Netrunner]]\n*[[Asalto]]\n*[[Backgammon]]\n*[[BattleLore (board game)]]\n*[[Battleship (game)|Battleship]]\n*[[Blockade (board game)|Blockade]]\n*[[Blood Bowl]]\n*[[Bul (game)|Bul]]\n*[[